name: Birthday Bones
author: Tami
summary: These cookies are great for your favorite furry friend.  Every dog I have given these to loves them.  It is nice to use doggie type cookie cutters, like bones or fire hydrants.
directions: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C)
Stir together the flour and baking powder; set aside
In a medium bowl, mix together the peanut butter and milk
Stir in the flour mixture until well blended
Turn out dough onto a lightly floured surface and knead until smooth
Roll out to 1/4 inch thickness and cut into shapes using cookie cutters
Place 2 inches apart onto the prepared cookie sheets
Bake for 20 minutes in the preheated oven, or until lightly brown
Remove from cookie sheets to cool on wire racks
